  "title": "Accounts & Admin Assistant (Accounts Payable)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a meticulous Accounts & Admin Assistant (Accounts Payable) to support our finance and administrative functions in the construction industry.</p><p>The ideal candidate should be organized, proactive, and familiar with construction-related accounting and administrative tasks.</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Handle accounts payables, invoicing, and bank reconciliations</li><li>Assist in progress claims, variation orders, and project cost tracking</li><li>Maintain accurate financial records and assist with monthly closing</li><li>Support ordering of materials and stock, procurement, supplier management, and inventory tracking</li><li>Ensure proper documentation of contracts, purchase orders, and safety records</li><li>Liaise with subcontractors, suppliers, and government agencies</li><li>Handle general office administration and ad-hoc tasks</li><li>Financial schedule and support Audit process</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Accounting, Business Administration, or related field</li><li>1-3 years of experience in construction or related industries preferred</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Excel and accounting software (e.g., Xero)</li><li>Knowledge of BCA guidelines, MOM regulations, and industry-related compliance is a plus</li><li>Strong attention to detail, ability to multitask and work in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul>",
